oai_dc:dc.dc:title: AN ANALYTICAL MODEL FOR OCEAN WAVE-SOIL-CAISSON INTERACTION
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Tsai, Yau-Tang
McDougal, William G.
Sollitt, Charles K.
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: wave-soil-caisson interaction
analytical model
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: An analytical model is developed to predict the soil responses induced by waves and caisson motion. The caisson is founded on a rubble bedding layer overlying a soil of finite depth. The responses are modeled by the Blot consolidation equations. Two approximations are employed to reduce mathematical difficulties: 1) a boundary layer approximation^ to decouple pore pressure and soil motion in the Blot equations and 2) a contact solution approximation for a thin elastic layer to address mixed-type boundary-value problems.
oai_dc:dc.dc:source: Coastal Engineering Proceedings; No. 20 (1986): Proceedings of 20th Conference on Coastal Engineering, Taipei, Taiwan, 1986.; 170
